#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:5
msgid "Jobs: pausing and resuming crawls"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:7
msgid ""
"Sometimes, for big sites, it's desirable to pause crawls and be able to "
"resume them later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:10
msgid ""
"Scrapy supports this functionality out of the box by providing the following "
"facilities:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:13
msgid "a scheduler that persists scheduled requests on disk"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:15
msgid "a duplicates filter that persists visited requests on disk"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:17
msgid ""
"an extension that keeps some spider state (key/value pairs) persistent "
"between batches"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:23
msgid "Job directory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:25
msgid ""
"To enable persistence support, define a *job directory* through the :setting:"
"`JOBDIR` setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:28
msgid ""
"The job directory will store all required data to keep the state of a "
"*single* job (i.e. a spider run), so that if stopped cleanly, it can be "
"resumed later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:31
msgid ""
"This directory must *not* be shared by different spiders, or even different "
"jobs of the same spider."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:34
msgid ""
"Treat the job directory with the same security care as your Scrapy project "
"source code. Do not point ``JOBDIR`` to a path that untrusted parties can "
"write to."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:38
msgid "See also :ref:`job-dir-contents`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:41
msgid "How to use it"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:43
msgid "To start a spider with persistence support enabled, run it like this::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:45 ../../../topics/jobs.rst:50
msgid "scrapy crawl somespider -s JOBDIR=crawls/somespider-1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:47
msgid ""
"Then, you can stop the spider safely at any time (by pressing Ctrl-C or "
"sending a signal), and resume it later by issuing the same command::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:55
msgid "Keeping persistent state between batches"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:57
msgid ""
"Sometimes you'll want to keep some persistent spider state between pause/"
"resume batches. You can use the ``spider.state`` attribute for that, which "
"should be a dict. There's :ref:`a built-in extension <topics-extensions-ref-"
"spiderstate>` that takes care of serializing, storing and loading that "
"attribute from the job directory, when the spider starts and stops."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:63
msgid ""
"Here's an example of a callback that uses the spider state (other spider "
"code is omitted for brevity):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:66
msgid ""
"def parse_item(self, response):\n"
"    # parse item here\n"
"    self.state[\"items_count\"] = self.state.get(\"items_count\", 0) + 1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:73
msgid "Persistence gotchas"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:75
msgid ""
"There are a few things to keep in mind if you want to be able to use the "
"Scrapy persistence support:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:79
msgid "Pause limitations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:81
msgid ""
"Job pausing and resuming is only supported when the spider is paused by "
"stopping it cleanly. Forced, sudden or otherwise unclean shutdown can lead "
"to data corruption in the job directory, which may prevent the spider from "
"resuming correctly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:87
msgid "Cookies expiration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:89
msgid ""
"Cookies may expire. So, if you don't resume your spider quickly the requests "
"scheduled may no longer work. This won't be an issue if your spider doesn't "
"rely on cookies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:96
msgid "Request serialization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:98
msgid ""
"For persistence to work, :class:`~scrapy.Request` objects must be "
"serializable with :mod:`pickle`, except for the ``callback`` and ``errback`` "
"values passed to their ``__init__`` method, which must be methods of the "
"running :class:`~scrapy.Spider` class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:103
msgid ""
"If you wish to log the requests that couldn't be serialized, you can set "
"the :setting:`SCHEDULER_DEBUG` setting to ``True`` in the project's settings "
"page. It is ``False`` by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:110
msgid "Job directory contents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:112
msgid ""
"The contents of a job directory depend on the components used during the "
"job. Components known to write in the job directory include the :ref:"
"`scheduler <topics-scheduler>` and the :class:`~scrapy.extensions."
"spiderstate.SpiderState` extension. See the reference documentation of the "
"corresponding components for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:118
msgid ""
"For example, with default settings, the job directory may look like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:120
msgid ""
"├── requests.queue\n"
"|   ├── active.json\n"
"|   └── {hostname}-{hash}\n"
"|       └── {priority}{s?}\n"
"|           ├── q{00000}\n"
"|           └── info.json\n"
"├── requests.seen\n"
"└── spider.state"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:131
msgid "Where:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:133
msgid ""
":class:`~scrapy.core.scheduler.Scheduler` creates the ``requests.queue/`` "
"directory and the ``active.json`` file, the latter containing the state data "
"returned by :meth:`DownloaderAwarePriorityQueue.close() <scrapy.pqueues."
"DownloaderAwarePriorityQueue.close>` the last time the job was paused."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:139
msgid ""
":class:`~scrapy.pqueues.DownloaderAwarePriorityQueue` creates the "
"``{hostname}-{hash}`` directories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:142
msgid ""
":class:`~scrapy.pqueues.ScrapyPriorityQueue` creates the ``{priority}{s?}`` "
"directories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:145
msgid ""
":class:`scrapy.squeues.PickleLifoDiskQueue`, a subclass of :class:`queuelib."
"LifoDiskQueue` that uses :mod:`pickle` to serialize :class:`dict` "
"representations of :class:`scrapy.Request` objects, creates the ``info."
"json`` and ``q{00000}`` files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:150
msgid ""
":class:`~scrapy.dupefilters.RFPDupeFilter` creates the ``requests.seen`` "
"file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/jobs.rst:153
msgid ""
":class:`~scrapy.extensions.spiderstate.SpiderState` creates the ``spider."
"state`` file."
msgstr ""
